  A description of an algorithm for solving the linear multiple-choice knapsack problem is given. The algorithm has a convenient structure for a branch-and bound approach to the multiple-choice knapsack problem. Keywords multiple-choice knapsack problem ; median finding in ordered sets [1] A.V Aho, J.E Hopcroft, J.D Ullman The design and analysis of computer algorithms Addison-Wesley, Reading, MA (1974) [2] E Balas, E Zemel An algorithm for large zero-one knapsack problems Oper. Res., 28 (1980), pp. 1132–1154 [3] M.E Dyer An O( n ) algorithm for the multiple-choice knapsack linear program Mathematical Programming, 29 (1984), pp. 57–63 [4] G.N Frederickson, D.B Johnson The complexity of selection and ranking in X + Y and matrices with sorted columns J. Comput. System Sci., 24 (1982), pp. 197–208 [5] E.L Johnson, M.W Padberg A note on the knapsack problem with special ordered sets Oper. Res. Lett., 1 (1981), pp. 18–22 [6] P Sinha, A.A Zoltners The multiple choice knapsack problem Oper. Res., 27 (1979), pp. 503–515 [7] E Zemel The linear multiple choice knapsack problem Oper. Res., 28 (1980), pp. 1412–1423 Copyright © 1984 Published by Elsevier B.V.